<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code calls strlen(username) and strlen(realm) without any runtime verification that the pointers are non-NULL and point to NUL-terminated character arrays. If a caller passes username or realm as NULL (strlen(NULL) undefined) or passes a buffer that is not NUL-terminated (strlen scans past the object bounds looking for '\0'), strlen can access memory beyond the referenced objects and violate Rule 21.17. Note: the subsequent calc_userhash only asserts username != NULL (mhd_assert), which is not a runtime guarantee in production builds.
</scenario>
